Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.  COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  4 years with Zero days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  2 years; EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  2 years.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2  years.

Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
- No Condition Time
- AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment
- Absolute Sobriety
- No drugs without a valid prescription
- Random screens

- Seek/Maintain employment or school or combination of employment and school for a minimum of 40 hours per week
